law.text:
The Long-Term Care Coordinating Council shall have the following duties:
To develop a statewide policy for the provision of long-term care and supervise the implementation of such policy;
To coordinate the activities of the cabinet with respect to long-term care;
To prepare an annual report on long-term care to the General Assembly and to the Governor containing the following:
The status of implementation of the state long-term care policy;
An appraisal of the problems of residents of long-term care facilities;
An overview of the activities of the council; and
Recommendations for improving the quality and delivery of long-term care services in the Commonwealth.
